cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on robust face recognition using sparse representation of high-dimensional facial images. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of sparsity-based classification framework in face recognition. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with compressive sensing theory and L1-minimization. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper discusses the numerical implementation of algorithms for L1-minimization. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper deals with facial images and their processing for recognition purposes.
